South African President, Cyril Ramaphosa on Monday apologised to President Muhammadu Buhari over xenophobic attacks on Nigerians in South Africa. Many Nigerians had lost their lives and properties due to the increasing xenophobic attacks in the country. Two Special envoys from South Africa delivered Ramaphosaâ€™s message to Buhari during a closed door meeting in Aso Rock. One of the special envoy, Jeff Radebe briefed State House correspondents at the end of the meeting.